A Magistratesâ€™ court sitting in Osogbo, Osun state on Wednesday ordered the remand of a 40-year-old herder, Mohamodu Umar, for alleged damage of a farm. The prosecutor, Sergeant Adepoju Kayode informed the court that the accused person committed the offence on February 7, 2020, at Egbedi, in Egbeda Local Government area of Osun State. He added that Umar maliciously entered the farm belonging to one Alhaji Isah Salawudeen with his cows and destroyed Maize and cassava valued at three million naira (#3,000,000). The accused person pleaded not guilty to one count charge levelled against him by the police. The defence counsel, R. A. Ngwu prayed the court to grant his client bail in the most liberal term. The Magistrate, A. O. Ajanaku, however, ordered that the accused person be remanded in police custody. She adjourned the matter till February 13, 2020, for hearing.